Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}. Slice @tomato{1} into 1⁄2-inch-thick rounds; season with salt and pepper. Halve @brioche buns{2}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @beef stock concentrate{1} and 3⁄4 cup water (11⁄2 cups for 4 servings).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, 2 tsp water (4 tsp for 4 servings), salt (we used 3⁄4 tsp; 11⁄4 tsp for 4), and pepper.

Form mixture into two patties (four patties for 4), each slightly wider than a burger bun.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer patties to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in pan used for patties over medium heat. Add shallot and @flour{1%tbsp}; cook, stirring constantly, until flour is lightly browned, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Gradually whisk in stock; bring to a simmer.

Add as much @truffle seasoning{2%g} as you like; cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes} more. (Reserve any remaining truffle seasoning for another use.)

Remove from heat and stir in @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, add a splash of water.

Toast buns until golden.

Fill buns with tomato slices and patties; spoon as much truffle sauce as you like over patties. Close to form burgers.

Divide burgers and potato wedges between plates. Serve with any remaining truffle sauce on the side for dipping.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.